You are working on siwx-oidc, a CAIP-122 to OpenID Connect bridge server.

## Workspace

Three Rust crates in one workspace:
- siwx-core (siwx-core/) — Pure crypto traits and implementations. No async.
- siwx-oidc (src/) — Axum OIDC server with Redis.
- siwx-oidc-auth (siwx-oidc-auth/) — Headless client, library + CLI.

## Architecture

Two-trait model:
- DIDMethod (siwx-core/src/did_method.rs) — primary, server-visible. Implementations: PkhMethod, KeyMethod, PeerMethod.
- CipherSuite (siwx-core/src/cipher_suite.rs) — internal to did:pkh. Implementations: Eip155Suite, Ed25519Suite, P256Suite.

Registries: all_did_methods() and all_cipher_suites() are static vec constructors, not inventory/linkme.

Extension: one file + one line in the registry function.

## Key files

Server logic: src/oidc.rs (sign_in, token, userinfo, ES256 key wrapper)
Config: src/config.rs (supported_did_methods, supported_pkh_namespaces)
Routes: src/axum_lib.rs (startup validation, Axum routes)
DID dispatch: siwx-core/src/did_method.rs (DIDMethod trait, find_did_method())
Client: siwx-oidc-auth/src/lib.rs (SiwxKey, authenticate(), AuthTokens)

## Sign-in flow

GET /authorize → 303 redirect + session cookie → client signs CAIP-122 message
GET /sign_in with siwx cookie → find_did_method().verify() → 303 redirect with code
POST /token → ES256-signed ID token + access token

## Conventions

- sub claim = full DID string (e.g., did:pkh:eip155:1:0x...)
- Cookie name: siwx (not siwe), payload: { did, message, signature }
- Config prefix: SIWEOIDC_ (Figment, supports TOML + env vars)
- siwx-core is sync-only — no network, no async
- Crypto ported from aqua-rs-auth (../aqua-rs-auth) — not a dependency
- New DID methods are opt-in via supported_did_methods config
- PKCS#8 PEM is the canonical key format (auto-detects Ed25519 vs P-256)

## Testing

cargo test -p siwx-core  — all crypto tests, no Redis needed (57 tests)
cargo test --bin siwx-oidc  — server tests, needs Redis on localhost
cargo build --workspace  — full workspace build
